Deuteraphorura ameskoana (Beruete, Arbea & Jordana)
:
Arbea et al. , 2011
. Boletín de la Sociedad Entomológica Aragonesa (S.E.A.) , 48: 352
Studied material. Loc. 2. 2 ex. , 29.IX.1985 ( holotype and paratype ).

It is only known from the type locality, Akuandi cave, in the Sierra de Urbasa, Navarra ( Beruete 2000a ,
Beruete et al. 2001
,
Beruete et al. 2002
,
Jordana et al. 2012
). It has been found on remains of decomposed wood, in very humid areas of the cavity.
